The '''Sharlissian Trade Corridor''' was a [[Hyperspace route/Legends|trade route]] located in the [[Mayagil sector/Legends|Mayagil]] and [[Bon'nyuw-Luq sector/Legends|Bon'nyuw-Luq]] [[Sector/Legends|sectors]] of the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories]].

==Astrography==
The Sharlissian Trade Corridor connected the [[Mayagil sector/Legends|Mayagil sector]] and the [[Bon'nyuw-Luq sector/Legends|Bon'nyuw-Luq sector]], two [[Sector/Legends|sectors]] of the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories]].<ref name="EAOC" /> This [[Hyperspace route/Legends|trade route]] began at [[Triton/Legends|Triton]], passed through [[Xagobah/Legends|Xagobah]], [[Kabal/Legends|Kabal]] and [[Nellac Kram]], and ended at the [[Sharlissia system/Legends|Sharlissia system]]. It intersected the [[Rimma Trade Route/Legends|Rimma Trade Route]] at Triton, and the [[Sanrafsix Corridor]] at Kabal.<ref name="TEA" />

==History==
In the [[Standard year/Legends|years]] following the [[Invasion of Naboo/Legends|Invasion of Naboo]], the trade route was heavily taxed by the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]]. As a result, the [[Trade Federation/Legends|Trade Federation]] discontinued operations to [[Kabal/Legends|Kabal]], leading to [[Foodstuff/Legends|food]] shortages. In [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]], a rash of food [[riot]]s swept the [[Planet/Legends|planet]].<ref name="Hnn46">{{HoloNetNewsWeb|46|regional/1337_3.html|Riots Rock Kabal}}</ref><ref name="Hnn51">{{HoloNetNewsWeb|51|regional/13411_2.html|Kabal Riots Quelled by Separatists; 4 Jedi Among the Dead}}</ref>

